sg3_utils|-----handy-ruler------------------------------------------------------|
sg3_utils: sg3_utils (Utilities for devices that use SCSI command sets)
sg3_utils:
sg3_utils: Collection of Linux utilities for devices that use the SCSI command
sg3_utils: set.
sg3_utils: Includes utilities to copy data based on "dd" syntax and semantics
sg3_utils: (called sg_dd, sgp_dd and sgm_dd); check INQUIRY data and VPD pages
sg3_utils: (sg_inq); check mode and log pages (sginfo, sg_modes and sg_logs);
sg3_utils: spin up and down disks (sg_start); do self tests (sg_senddiag); and
sg3_utils: various other functions.
sg3_utils: http://sg.torque.net/sg/sg3_utils.html
sg3_utils: Packager: _PACKAGER on _BUILD_DATE
